So, I understand historical Russian lands, Donbass bombed 8 years lalalala. But honestly, do Russians think their lives have improved since 2014, and now 2022? It seemed like NATO was becoming unnecessary and a thing of the past, Russia was developing and the trade between Russia and Europe was beneficial, Europe could even be played off of the U.S as they were even skeptical. Nobody was going to let Ukraine into NATO and Germany + France even vetoed it, things were going well for Russia. But then the great multi-move seizure of Crimea by force and initiation of the conflict in Donbass. So what did Russia gain by this? 2 more subsidized regions that drain money from the coffers and massively reduced relations with the Europeans. Now this was bad enough, but at least the Europeans were still happy to be addicted to Russian gas and although the Russian economy stagnated, at least there was some level of cooperation. Now this whole new "special military operation" was a completely new level of strategic blunder, Europeans for the most part despite what you might read on RT now see Russia as a horde of barbarians and don't want anything to do with you, and the U.S got to swoop in and help Ukraine + reinforce Europe reinforcing their hegemony there. Now Russia is in an attritional proxy war with both the U.S and what could have been their European allies to take more of what will be destroyed and subsidized land that will further waste money from the coffers. And Europeans, despite what Russian propaganda might tell you, are working with caucuses, north Africa, Canada & US (LNG), middle east (LNG) to get their gas + oil supplies meaning Russia will be forced to sell at below market rates. And now Russia is essentially going to become a Chinese vassal state giving raw materials as realistically they're the only viable alternative to western countries for any advanced production of things like semiconductors. Let's just say China decides it wants to return Vladivostok (they still call it Haishenwai) as they've been intent on returning anything taken by them through "unequal treaties" and it was taken in 1860. What does Russia do? If it loses trade with China then it can only trade with third world countries like Iran and North Korea so ironically Russia has become more vulnerable. It just doesn't make any sense from a strategic standpoint, you have made the U.S stronger and Russia weaker. Does nobody over there think about this? Is it better to live like a Hermit kingdom to grow 1% larger adding new lands that will be subsidized in perpetuity anyways?
